source("eqcut.r")
split.x <- function(x) {
  x <- na.omit(x)
  c(min(x), quantile(x, probs=(1:2)/3), max(x))
}
effICGI <- read.csv("ICGI.csv")
effICGI <- effICGI %>%
  filter(!is.na(ICGI))%>%
  filter(!is.na(AUC))
effICGI$DOSE <- factor(effICGI$XDL1)

simplelogisticplot<- ggplot(effICGI,aes(AUC,ICGI))+
  geom_smooth(method="glm",method.args = list(family = "binomial"),
              color="black")+
  geom_point(position=position_jitter(height=0.025),aes(col=DOSE))
simplelogisticplot

We do some calculation to better understand the data. We bin the AUC into three equal groups, compute the bin mean and intercept, then we compute the percentage of response in each bin along the standard error

effICGI$AUC.int <- eqcut(effICGI$AUC, ngroups=3,builtinlabels=FALSE,
     withhold = list(Placebo = (effICGI$AUC==0)))
effICGI$AUC.intmean <- tapply(effICGI$AUC, effICGI$AUC.int, mean)[effICGI$AUC.int]
xintercept <- split.x(effICGI$AUC[effICGI$AUC > 0])
# we also add mean auc in each bin and where the bin starts these will
#be useful later in the plot

# compute the probability of response and associated standard error in each bin
observedprobsbuaucbin <- effICGI %>%
  group_by(AUC.int,AUC.intmean)%>%
  summarize(N=sum(ICGI,na.rm=TRUE),
            Nmiss= length(AUC.int[is.na(AUC.int)]),
            Ntot=n(),
            prob=N/Ntot,
            SE= sqrt(prob*(1-prob)/Ntot ))
knitr::kable(observedprobsbuaucbin)

we now want to compute all t he sta ts of AU C by do se level we want to also compute the percentage of AUC distribution that crosses the AUC bins 
effICGIaucstatsbydose <- effICGI %>%
  group_by(DOSE)%>%
  dplyr::summarize(
  minauc = min(AUC),
  maxauc = max(AUC),
  medauc = median(AUC),
  twentyfifth  = quantile(AUC,0.25),
  seventyfifth = quantile(AUC,0.75),
  ninety  = quantile(AUC,0.90),
  tenth = quantile(AUC,0.10),
  N = sum(ICGI,na.rm=TRUE),
  Nmiss = length(AUC.int[is.na(AUC.int)]),
  Ntot = n(),
  prob = N/Ntot,
  SE = sqrt(prob*(1-prob)/Ntot ))

xintercept<- as.vector(xintercept)
percentcrossingaucbins <- effICGI %>%
  group_by(DOSE) %>%
  summarize(totalN=n(),
            N0= length(AUC[AUC >= 0 & AUC < xintercept[1]] )/totalN,
            N1= length(AUC[AUC >= xintercept[1]& AUC < xintercept[2]] )/totalN,
            N2= length(AUC[AUC >= xintercept[2]& AUC < xintercept[3]] )/totalN,
            N3= length(AUC[AUC >= xintercept[3]& AUC < xintercept[4]] )/totalN
            )
effICGIaucstatsbydose<- left_join(effICGIaucstatsbydose,percentcrossingaucbins)

effICGIaucstatsbydose$ypointsdose <-
  ifelse(effICGIaucstatsbydose$DOSE=="Placebo"  , -0.55,
         ifelse(effICGIaucstatsbydose$DOSE=="600 mg", -0.45,
                ifelse(effICGIaucstatsbydose$DOSE=="1200 mg",-0.35,
                       ifelse(effICGIaucstatsbydose$DOSE=="1800 mg",-0.25,
                              ifelse(effICGIaucstatsbydose$DOSE=="2400 mg",-0.15,-1.05)))))

  Predict(lrmmodel,fun=plogis,AUC=effICGIaucstatsbydose$twentyfifth))

alltogether <-  ggplot(effICGI, aes(AUC,ICGI) )+
  geom_vline(xintercept=xintercept,linetype=2)+
  geom_hline(yintercept=c(0,1))+
  geom_smooth(data=effICGI,method="glm",method.args = list(family = "binomial"),
              color="black",aes(fill="Logistic Fit 95% CI"))+
  geom_pointrange(data=observedprobsbuaucbin,aes(
    linetype="Observed probability by AUC bin",
    x=as.double(as.character(AUC.intmean)),
    y=prob,ymin=prob+2*SE,ymax=prob-2*SE) )+
  geom_point(data=effICGIaucstatsbydose,aes(medauc,y=prob,col=factor(DOSE)),
             size=4,alpha=0.5)+  
  geom_linerangeh(data=effICGIaucstatsbydose,size=2,alpha=0.6,
                  aes(xmin=minauc,xmax=maxauc,
                      y=ypointsdose,x=NULL,
                      col= DOSE,group=DOSE),position=position_dodgev(height=0.5))+
  geom_linerangeh(data=effICGIaucstatsbydose,size=2.5,alpha=0.6,
                  aes(xmin=twentyfifth,xmax=seventyfifth,
                      y=ypointsdose,x=NULL,col= DOSE,group=DOSE),
                  position=position_dodgev(height=0.5))+
  geom_point(data=effICGIaucstatsbydose,size=3,alpha=0.6,aes(x=medauc,y=ypointsdose,col=DOSE),
             position=position_dodgev(height=0.5))+
  geom_text(data=observedprobsbuaucbin,y=0.1,aes(
              x=as.double(as.character(AUC.intmean)),
              label=paste(AUC.int,"\n",Ntot,"\n",N,"\n",100*round(prob,2),"%"
                          ,sep="")))+
  geom_text(data=observedprobsbuaucbin,x=250,y=0.1,
            label=paste("AUC bins","\n","Total N", "\n", "Responders","\n","Percentage",sep=""
            ))+
   geom_density_ridges2(data=ggridgedata,aes(AUC,y=ypointsdose,group=DOSE,col=DOSE),
                        rel_min_height = 0.005,alpha=0.1,scale = 1.2,
                        quantile_lines = TRUE, quantiles = c(0.1,0.25, 0.5, 0.75,0.9),
                        position=position_dodgev(height=0.2))+
  geom_point(data=ggridgedata,aes(AUC,y=ypointsdose-0.02,group=DOSE,col=DOSE),
             alpha=0.4,size=2)+
    geom_label(data=effICGIaucstatsbydose,x=26.67016 ,aes(y=ypointsdose-0.03, col=factor(DOSE),
                                                  label=round(100*N1,0)),
             size=5,alpha=0.5,show.legend = FALSE)+
    geom_label(data=effICGIaucstatsbydose,x=83,aes(y=ypointsdose-0.03 ,col=factor(DOSE),
                                                  label=round(100*N2,0)),
             size=5,alpha=0.5,show.legend = FALSE)+
    geom_label(data=effICGIaucstatsbydose,x=223,aes(y=ypointsdose-0.03 ,col=factor(DOSE),
                                                  label=round(100*N3,0)),
             size=5,alpha=0.5,show.legend = FALSE)+
  
  labs(x="AUC µg*h/mL",y="Pr(Response)",colour="Observed probability by Dose")+
  scale_x_continuous(breaks=seq(0,350,25))+
  scale_y_continuous(breaks=c(-0.55,-0.45,-0.35,-0.25,-0.15,0,0.25,0.50,0.75,1.0),
                     labels=c("Placebo","600 mg","1200 mg","1800 mg","2400 mg","0","0.25","0.50","0.75","1"))+
  coord_cartesian(xlim=c(-5,350),ylim=c(-0.55,1))+
  scale_fill_manual("",breaks="Logistic Fit 95% CI",values="gray")+
  scale_linetype_manual("",breaks="Observed probability by AUC bin",values=1)+
  scale_shape_manual("",breaks="Observed probability by AUC bin",values=1)+
  guides(colour=guide_legend(nrow=1))+
  theme_bw(base_size = 16)+
  theme(legend.position="top",
        axis.title.y = element_text(
          margin = unit(c(0, 7, 0, 0), "mm"), angle = 90)
  )+
  ggthemes::scale_colour_tableau()
